9 // This library implements `print` family of functions in classes like ----
10 // Module, Function, Value, etc. In-memory representation of those classes is ----
11 // converted to IR strings. ----
12 // ----
13 // Note that these routines must be extremely tolerant of various errors in the ----
14 // LLVM code, because it can be used for debugging transformations. ----

103 /// Look for a value that might be wrapped as metadata, e.g. a value in a ----
104 /// metadata operand. Returns the input value as-is if it is not wrapped. ----
105 static const Value *skipMetadataWrapper(const Value *V) { 0
106 if (const auto *MAV = dyn_cast(V)) 0
107 if (const auto *VAM = dyn_cast(MAV->getMetadata())) 0
108 return VAM->getValue(); 0
109 return V; 0
110 } ----

112 static void orderValue(const Value *V, OrderMap &OM) { 0
113 if (OM.lookup(V)) 0
114 return; 0
115 ----
116 if (const Constant *C = dyn_cast(V)) 0
117 if (C->getNumOperands() && !isa(C)) 0
118 for (const Value *Op : C->operands()) 0
119 if (!isa(Op) && !isa(Op)) 0
120 orderValue(Op, OM); 0
121 ----
122 // Note: we cannot cache this lookup above, since inserting into the map ----
123 // changes the map's size, and thus affects the other IDs. ----
124 unsigned ID = OM.size() + 1; 0
125 OM[V] = ID; 0
126 } ----
127 ----
128 static OrderMap orderModule(const Module *M) { 0
129 OrderMap OM; 0
130 ----
131 for (const GlobalVariable &G : M->globals()) { 0
132 if (G.hasInitializer()) 0
133 if (!isa(G.getInitializer())) 0
134 orderValue(G.getInitializer(), OM); 0
135 orderValue(&G, OM); 0
136 } ----
137 for (const GlobalAlias &A : M->aliases()) { 0
138 if (!isa(A.getAliasee())) 0
139 orderValue(A.getAliasee(), OM); 0
140 orderValue(&A, OM); 0
141 } ----
142 for (const GlobalIFunc &I : M->ifuncs()) { 0
143 if (!isa(I.getResolver())) 0
144 orderValue(I.getResolver(), OM); 0
145 orderValue(&I, OM); 0
146 } ----
147 for (const Function &F : *M) { 0
148 for (const Use &U : F.operands()) 0
149 if (!isa(U.get())) 0
150 orderValue(U.get(), OM); 0
151 ----
152 orderValue(&F, OM); 0
153 ----
154 if (F.isDeclaration()) 0
155 continue; 0
156 ----
157 for (const Argument &A : F.args()) 0
158 orderValue(&A, OM); 0
159 for (const BasicBlock &BB : F) { 0
160 orderValue(&BB, OM); 0
161 for (const Instruction &I : BB) { 0
162 for (const Value *Op : I.operands()) { 0
163 Op = skipMetadataWrapper(Op); 0
164 if ((isa(*Op) && !isa(*Op)) || 0
165 isa(*Op)) 0
166 orderValue(Op, OM); 0
167 } ----
168 orderValue(&I, OM); 0
169 } ----
170 } ----
171 } ----
172 return OM; 0
173 } ----

175 static std::vector ----
176 predictValueUseListOrder(const Value *V, unsigned ID, const OrderMap &OM) { 0
177 // Predict use-list order for this one. ----
178 using Entry = std::pair; ----
179 SmallVector List; 0
180 for (const Use &U : V->uses()) 0
181 // Check if this user will be serialized. ----
182 if (OM.lookup(U.getUser())) 0
183 List.push_back(std::make_pair(&U, List.size())); 0
184 ----
185 if (List.size() < 2) 0
186 // We may have lost some users. ----
187 return {}; 0
188 ----
189 // When referencing a value before its declaration, a temporary value is ----
190 // created, which will later be RAUWed with the actual value. This reverses ----
191 // the use list. This happens for all values apart from basic blocks. ----
192 bool GetsReversed = !isa(V); 0
193 if (auto *BA = dyn_cast(V)) 0
194 ID = OM.lookup(BA->getBasicBlock()); 0
195 llvm::sort(List, [&](const Entry &L, const Entry &R) { 0
196 const Use *LU = L.first; 0
197 const Use *RU = R.first; 0
198 if (LU == RU) 0
199 return false; 0
200 ----
201 auto LID = OM.lookup(LU->getUser()); 0
202 auto RID = OM.lookup(RU->getUser()); 0
203 ----
204 // If ID is 4, then expect: 7 6 5 1 2 3. ----
205 if (LID < RID) { 0
206 if (GetsReversed) 0
207 if (RID <= ID) 0
208 return true; 0
209 return false; 0
210 } ----
211 if (RID < LID) { 0
212 if (GetsReversed) 0
213 if (LID <= ID) 0
214 return false; 0
215 return true; 0
216 } ----
217 ----
218 // LID and RID are equal, so we have different operands of the same user. ----
219 // Assume operands are added in order for all instructions. ----
220 if (GetsReversed) 0
221 if (LID <= ID) 0
222 return LU->getOperandNo() < RU->getOperandNo(); 0
223 return LU->getOperandNo() > RU->getOperandNo(); 0
224 }); ----
225 ----
226 if (llvm::is_sorted(List, llvm::less_second())) 0
227 // Order is already correct. ----
228 return {}; 0
229 ----
230 // Store the shuffle. ----
231 std::vector Shuffle(List.size()); 0
232 for (size_t I = 0, E = List.size(); I != E; ++I) 0
233 Shuffle[I] = List[I].second; 0
234 return Shuffle; 0
235 } 0

237 static UseListOrderMap predictUseListOrder(const Module *M) { 0
238 OrderMap OM = orderModule(M); 0
239 UseListOrderMap ULOM; 0
240 for (const auto &Pair : OM) { 0
241 const Value *V = Pair.first; 0
242 if (V->use_empty() || std::next(V->use_begin()) == V->use_end()) 0
243 continue; 0
244 ----
245 std::vector Shuffle = ----
246 predictValueUseListOrder(V, Pair.second, OM); 0
247 if (Shuffle.empty()) 0
248 continue; 0
249 ----
250 const Function *F = nullptr; 0
251 if (auto *I = dyn_cast(V)) 0
252 F = I->getFunction(); 0
253 if (auto *A = dyn_cast(V)) 0
254 F = A->getParent(); 0
255 if (auto *BB = dyn_cast(V)) 0
256 F = BB->getParent(); 0
257 ULOM[F][V] = std::move(Shuffle); 0
258 } 0
259 return ULOM; 0
260 } 0

262 static const Module *getModuleFromVal(const Value *V) { 0
263 if (const Argument *MA = dyn_cast(V)) 0
264 return MA->getParent() ? MA->getParent()->getParent() : nullptr; 0
265 ----
266 if (const BasicBlock *BB = dyn_cast(V)) 0
267 return BB->getParent() ? BB->getParent()->getParent() : nullptr; 0
268 ----
269 if (const Instruction *I = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
270 const Function *M = I->getParent() ? I->getParent()->getParent() : nullptr; 0
271 return M ? M->getParent() : nullptr; 0
272 } ----
273 ----
274 if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast(V)) 0
275 return GV->getParent(); 0
276 ----
277 if (const auto *MAV = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
278 for (const User *U : MAV->users()) 0
279 if (isa(U)) 0
280 if (const Module *M = getModuleFromVal(U)) 0
281 return M; 0
282 return nullptr; 0
283 } ----
284 ----
285 return nullptr; 0
286 } ----

494 ----
495 std::vector &TypePrinting::getNumberedTypes() { 0
496 incorporateTypes(); 0
497 ----
498 // We know all the numbers that each type is used and we know that it is a ----
499 // dense assignment. Convert the map to an index table, if it's not done ----
500 // already (judging from the sizes): ----
501 if (NumberedTypes.size() == Type2Number.size()) 0
502 return NumberedTypes; 0
503 ----
504 NumberedTypes.resize(Type2Number.size()); 0
505 for (const auto &P : Type2Number) { 0
506 assert(P.second < NumberedTypes.size() && "Didn't get a dense numbering?"); 0
507 assert(!NumberedTypes[P.second] && "Didn't get a unique numbering?"); 0
508 NumberedTypes[P.second] = P.first; 0
509 } ----
510 return NumberedTypes; 0
511 } ----

513 bool TypePrinting::empty() { 0
514 incorporateTypes(); 0
515 return NamedTypes.empty() && Type2Number.empty(); 0
516 } ----
517 ----
518 void TypePrinting::incorporateTypes() { 0
519 if (!DeferredM) 0
520 return; 0
521 ----
522 NamedTypes.run(*DeferredM, false); 0
523 DeferredM = nullptr; 0
524 ----
525 // The list of struct types we got back includes all the struct types, split ----
526 // the unnamed ones out to a numbering and remove the anonymous structs. ----
527 unsigned NextNumber = 0; 0
528 ----
529 std::vector::iterator NextToUse = NamedTypes.begin(); 0
530 for (StructType *STy : NamedTypes) { 0
531 // Ignore anonymous types. ----
532 if (STy->isLiteral()) 0
533 continue; 0
534 ----
535 if (STy->getName().empty()) 0
536 Type2Number[STy] = NextNumber++; 0
537 else ----
538 *NextToUse++ = STy; 0
539 } ----
540 ----
541 NamedTypes.erase(NextToUse, NamedTypes.end()); 0
542 } ----

544 /// Write the specified type to the specified raw_ostream, making use of type ----
545 /// names or up references to shorten the type name where possible. ----
546 void TypePrinting::print(Type *Ty, raw_ostream &OS) { 0
547 switch (Ty->getTypeID()) { 0

549 case Type::HalfTyID: OS << "half"; return; 0

552 case Type::DoubleTyID: OS << "double"; return; 0

559 case Type::X86_AMXTyID: OS << "x86_amx"; return; 0
560 case Type::TokenTyID: OS << "token"; return; 0
561 case Type::IntegerTyID: 0

564 ----
565 case Type::FunctionTyID: { 0

583 return printStructBody(STy, OS); 0
584 ----
585 if (!STy->getName().empty()) 0
586 return PrintLLVMName(OS, STy->getName(), LocalPrefix); 0
587 ----
588 incorporateTypes(); 0
589 const auto I = Type2Number.find(STy); 0
590 if (I != Type2Number.end()) 0
591 OS << '%' << I->second; 0
592 else // Not enumerated, print the hex address. ----
593 OS << "%\"type " << STy << '\"'; 0
594 return; 0
595 } ----
596 case Type::PointerTyID: { 0
597 PointerType *PTy = cast(Ty); 0
598 OS << "ptr"; 0
599 if (unsigned AddressSpace = PTy->getAddressSpace()) 0
600 OS << " addrspace(" << AddressSpace << ')'; 0
601 return; 0
602 } ----
603 case Type::ArrayTyID: { 0
604 ArrayType *ATy = cast(Ty); 0
605 OS << '[' << ATy->getNumElements() << " x "; 0
606 print(ATy->getElementType(), OS); 0
607 OS << ']'; 0
608 return; 0
609 } ----
610 case Type::FixedVectorTyID: 0
611 case Type::ScalableVectorTyID: { ----
612 VectorType *PTy = cast(Ty); 0
613 ElementCount EC = PTy->getElementCount(); 0
614 OS << "<"; 0
615 if (EC.isScalable()) 0
616 OS << "vscale x "; 0
617 OS << EC.getKnownMinValue() << " x "; 0
618 print(PTy->getElementType(), OS); 0
619 OS << '>'; 0
620 return; 0
621 } ----
622 case Type::TypedPointerTyID: { 0
623 TypedPointerType *TPTy = cast(Ty); 0
624 OS << "typedptr(" << *TPTy->getElementType() << ", " 0
625 << TPTy->getAddressSpace() << ")"; 0
626 return; 0
627 } ----
628 case Type::TargetExtTyID: 0
629 TargetExtType *TETy = cast(Ty); 0
630 OS << "target(\""; 0
631 printEscapedString(Ty->getTargetExtName(), OS); 0
632 OS << "\""; 0
633 for (Type *Inner : TETy->type_params()) 0
634 OS << ", " << *Inner; 0
635 for (unsigned IntParam : TETy->int_params()) 0
636 OS << ", " << IntParam; 0
637 OS << ")"; 0
638 return; 0
639 } ----
640 llvm_unreachable("Invalid TypeID"); 0
641 } ----
642 ----
643 void TypePrinting::printStructBody(StructType *STy, raw_ostream &OS) { 0
644 if (STy->isOpaque()) { 0
645 OS << "opaque"; 0
646 return; 0
647 } ----
648 ----
649 if (STy->isPacked()) 0
650 OS << '<'; 0
651 ----
652 if (STy->getNumElements() == 0) { 0
653 OS << "{}"; 0
654 } else { ----
655 OS << "{ "; 0
656 ListSeparator LS; 0
657 for (Type *Ty : STy->elements()) { 0
658 OS << LS; 0
659 print(Ty, OS); 0
660 } ----
661 ----
662 OS << " }"; 0
663 } ----
664 if (STy->isPacked()) 0
665 OS << '>'; 0
666 } ----

675 /// This class provides computation of slot numbers for LLVM Assembly writing. ----
676 /// ----
677 class SlotTracker : public AbstractSlotTrackerStorage { ----

858 SlotTracker *ModuleSlotTracker::getMachine() { 0
859 if (!ShouldCreateStorage) 0
860 return Machine; 0
861 ----
862 ShouldCreateStorage = false; 0
863 MachineStorage = ----
864 std::make_unique(M, ShouldInitializeAllMetadata); 0
865 Machine = MachineStorage.get(); 0
866 if (ProcessModuleHookFn) 0
867 Machine->setProcessHook(ProcessModuleHookFn); 0
868 if (ProcessFunctionHookFn) 0
869 Machine->setProcessHook(ProcessFunctionHookFn); 0
870 return Machine; 0

873 void ModuleSlotTracker::incorporateFunction(const Function &F) { 0
874 // Using getMachine() may lazily create the slot tracker. ----
875 if (!getMachine()) 0
876 return; 0
877 ----
878 // Nothing to do if this is the right function already. ----
879 if (this->F == &F) 0
880 return; 0
881 if (this->F) 0
882 Machine->purgeFunction(); 0
883 Machine->incorporateFunction(&F); 0
884 this->F = &F; 0
885 } ----

904 static SlotTracker *createSlotTracker(const Value *V) { 0
905 if (const Argument *FA = dyn_cast(V)) 0
906 return new SlotTracker(FA->getParent()); 0
907 ----
908 if (const Instruction *I = dyn_cast(V)) 0
909 if (I->getParent()) 0
910 return new SlotTracker(I->getParent()->getParent()); 0
911 ----
912 if (const BasicBlock *BB = dyn_cast(V)) 0
913 return new SlotTracker(BB->getParent()); 0
914 ----
915 if (const GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast(V)) 0
916 return new SlotTracker(GV->getParent()); 0
917 ----
918 if (const GlobalAlias *GA = dyn_cast(V)) 0
919 return new SlotTracker(GA->getParent()); 0
920 ----
921 if (const GlobalIFunc *GIF = dyn_cast(V)) 0
922 return new SlotTracker(GIF->getParent()); 0
923 ----
924 if (const Function *Func = dyn_cast(V)) 0
925 return new SlotTracker(Func); 0
926 ----
927 return nullptr; 0
928 } ----

950 inline void SlotTracker::initializeIfNeeded() { 0
951 if (TheModule) { 0
952 processModule(); 0
953 TheModule = nullptr; ///< Prevent re-processing next time we're called. 0
954 } ----
955 ----
956 if (TheFunction && !FunctionProcessed) 0
957 processFunction(); 0
958 } 0
959 ----
960 int SlotTracker::initializeIndexIfNeeded() { 0
961 if (!TheIndex) 0
962 return 0; 0
963 int NumSlots = processIndex(); 0
964 TheIndex = nullptr; ///< Prevent re-processing next time we're called. 0
965 return NumSlots; 0
966 } ----
967 ----
968 // Iterate through all the global variables, functions, and global ----
969 // variable initializers and create slots for them. ----
970 void SlotTracker::processModule() { 0
971 ST_DEBUG("begin processModule!\n"); ----
972 ----
973 // Add all of the unnamed global variables to the value table. ----
974 for (const GlobalVariable &Var : TheModule->globals()) { 0
975 if (!Var.hasName()) 0
976 CreateModuleSlot(&Var); 0
977 processGlobalObjectMetadata(Var); 0
978 auto Attrs = Var.getAttributes(); 0
979 if (Attrs.hasAttributes()) 0
980 CreateAttributeSetSlot(Attrs); 0
981 } ----
982 ----
983 for (const GlobalAlias &A : TheModule->aliases()) { 0
984 if (!A.hasName()) 0
985 CreateModuleSlot(&A); 0
986 } ----
987 ----
988 for (const GlobalIFunc &I : TheModule->ifuncs()) { 0
989 if (!I.hasName()) 0
990 CreateModuleSlot(&I); 0
991 } ----
992 ----
993 // Add metadata used by named metadata. ----
994 for (const NamedMDNode &NMD : TheModule->named_metadata()) { 0
995 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NMD.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
996 CreateMetadataSlot(NMD.getOperand(i)); 0
997 } ----
998 ----
999 for (const Function &F : *TheModule) { 0
1000 if (!F.hasName()) 0
1001 // Add all the unnamed functions to the table. ----
1002 CreateModuleSlot(&F); 0
1003 ----
1004 if (ShouldInitializeAllMetadata) 0
1005 processFunctionMetadata(F); 0
1006 ----
1007 // Add all the function attributes to the table. ----
1008 // FIXME: Add attributes of other objects? ----
1009 AttributeSet FnAttrs = F.getAttributes().getFnAttrs(); 0
1010 if (FnAttrs.hasAttributes()) 0
1011 CreateAttributeSetSlot(FnAttrs); 0
1012 } ----
1013 ----
1014 if (ProcessModuleHookFn) 0
1015 ProcessModuleHookFn(this, TheModule, ShouldInitializeAllMetadata); 0
1016 ----
1017 ST_DEBUG("end processModule!\n"); ----
1018 } 0
1019 ----
1020 // Process the arguments, basic blocks, and instructions of a function. ----
1021 void SlotTracker::processFunction() { 0
1022 ST_DEBUG("begin processFunction!\n"); ----
1023 fNext = 0; 0
1024 ----
1025 // Process function metadata if it wasn't hit at the module-level. ----
1026 if (!ShouldInitializeAllMetadata) 0
1027 processFunctionMetadata(*TheFunction); 0
1028 ----
1029 // Add all the function arguments with no names. ----
1030 for(Function::const_arg_iterator AI = TheFunction->arg_begin(), 0
1031 AE = TheFunction->arg_end(); AI != AE; ++AI) 0
1032 if (!AI->hasName()) 0
1033 CreateFunctionSlot(&*AI); 0
1034 ----
1035 ST_DEBUG("Inserting Instructions:\n"); ----
1036 ----
1037 // Add all of the basic blocks and instructions with no names. ----
1038 for (auto &BB : *TheFunction) { 0
1039 if (!BB.hasName()) 0
1040 CreateFunctionSlot(&BB); 0
1041 ----
1042 for (auto &I : BB) { 0
1043 if (!I.getType()->isVoidTy() && !I.hasName()) 0
1044 CreateFunctionSlot(&I); 0
1045 ----
1046 // We allow direct calls to any llvm.foo function here, because the ----
1047 // target may not be linked into the optimizer. ----
1048 if (const auto *Call = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
1049 // Add all the call attributes to the table. ----
1050 AttributeSet Attrs = Call->getAttributes().getFnAttrs(); 0
1051 if (Attrs.hasAttributes()) 0
1052 CreateAttributeSetSlot(Attrs); 0
1053 } ----
1054 } ----
1055 } ----
1056 ----
1057 if (ProcessFunctionHookFn) 0
1058 ProcessFunctionHookFn(this, TheFunction, ShouldInitializeAllMetadata); 0
1059 ----
1060 FunctionProcessed = true; 0
1061 ----
1062 ST_DEBUG("end processFunction!\n"); ----
1063 } 0
1064 ----
1065 // Iterate through all the GUID in the index and create slots for them. ----
1066 int SlotTracker::processIndex() { 0
1067 ST_DEBUG("begin processIndex!\n"); ----
1068 assert(TheIndex); 0
1069 ----
1070 // The first block of slots are just the module ids, which start at 0 and are ----
1071 // assigned consecutively. Since the StringMap iteration order isn't ----
1072 // guaranteed, use a std::map to order by module ID before assigning slots. ----
1073 std::map ModuleIdToPathMap; 0
1074 for (auto &[ModPath, ModId] : TheIndex->modulePaths()) 0
1075 ModuleIdToPathMap[ModId.first] = ModPath; 0
1076 for (auto &ModPair : ModuleIdToPathMap) 0
1077 CreateModulePathSlot(ModPair.second); 0
1078 ----
1079 // Start numbering the GUIDs after the module ids. ----
1080 GUIDNext = ModulePathNext; 0
1081 ----
1082 for (auto &GlobalList : *TheIndex) 0
1083 CreateGUIDSlot(GlobalList.first); 0
1084 ----
1085 for (auto &TId : TheIndex->typeIdCompatibleVtableMap()) 0
1086 CreateGUIDSlot(GlobalValue::getGUID(TId.first)); 0
1087 ----
1088 // Start numbering the TypeIds after the GUIDs. ----
1089 TypeIdNext = GUIDNext; 0
1090 for (const auto &TID : TheIndex->typeIds()) 0
1091 CreateTypeIdSlot(TID.second.first); 0
1092 ----
1093 ST_DEBUG("end processIndex!\n"); ----
1094 return TypeIdNext; 0
1095 } 0
1096 ----
1097 void SlotTracker::processGlobalObjectMetadata(const GlobalObject &GO) { 0
1098 SmallVector, 4> MDs; 0
1099 GO.getAllMetadata(MDs); 0
1100 for (auto &MD : MDs) 0
1101 CreateMetadataSlot(MD.second); 0
1102 } 0
1103 ----
1104 void SlotTracker::processFunctionMetadata(const Function &F) { 0
1105 processGlobalObjectMetadata(F); 0
1106 for (auto &BB : F) { 0
1107 for (auto &I : BB) 0
1108 processInstructionMetadata(I); 0
1109 } ----
1110 } 0
1111 ----
1112 void SlotTracker::processInstructionMetadata(const Instruction &I) { 0
1113 // Process metadata used directly by intrinsics. ----
1114 if (const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast(&I)) 0
1115 if (Function *F = CI->getCalledFunction()) 0
1116 if (F->isIntrinsic()) 0
1117 for (auto &Op : I.operands()) 0
1118 if (auto *V = dyn_cast_or_null(Op)) 0
1119 if (MDNode *N = dyn_cast(V->getMetadata())) 0
1120 CreateMetadataSlot(N); 0
1121 ----
1122 // Process metadata attached to this instruction. ----
1123 SmallVector, 4> MDs; 0
1124 I.getAllMetadata(MDs); 0
1125 for (auto &MD : MDs) 0
1126 CreateMetadataSlot(MD.second); 0
1127 } 0
1128 ----
1129 /// Clean up after incorporating a function. This is the only way to get out of ----
1130 /// the function incorporation state that affects get*Slot/Create*Slot. Function ----
1131 /// incorporation state is indicated by TheFunction != 0. ----
1132 void SlotTracker::purgeFunction() { 0
1133 ST_DEBUG("begin purgeFunction!\n"); ----
1134 fMap.clear(); // Simply discard the function level map 0
1135 TheFunction = nullptr; 0
1136 FunctionProcessed = false; 0
1137 ST_DEBUG("end purgeFunction!\n"); ----
1138 } 0

1144 ----
1145 // Find the value in the module map ----
1146 ValueMap::iterator MI = mMap.find(V); 0
1147 return MI == mMap.end() ? -1 : (int)MI->second; 0
1148 } ----

1222 /// CreateModuleSlot - Insert the specified GlobalValue* into the slot table. ----
1223 void SlotTracker::CreateModuleSlot(const GlobalValue *V) { 0
1224 assert(V && "Can't insert a null Value into SlotTracker!"); 0
1225 assert(!V->getType()->isVoidTy() && "Doesn't need a slot!"); 0
1226 assert(!V->hasName() && "Doesn't need a slot!"); 0
1227 ----
1228 unsigned DestSlot = mNext++; 0
1229 mMap[V] = DestSlot; 0
1230 ----
1231 ST_DEBUG(" Inserting value [" << V->getType() << "] = " << V << " slot=" << ----
1232 DestSlot << " ["); ----
1233 // G = Global, F = Function, A = Alias, I = IFunc, o = other ----
1234 ST_DEBUG((isa(V) ? 'G' : ----
1235 (isa(V) ? 'F' : ----
1236 (isa(V) ? 'A' : ----
1237 (isa(V) ? 'I' : 'o')))) << "]\n"); ----
1238 } 0
1239 ----
1240 /// CreateSlot - Create a new slot for the specified value if it has no name. ----
1241 void SlotTracker::CreateFunctionSlot(const Value *V) { 0
1242 assert(!V->getType()->isVoidTy() && !V->hasName() && "Doesn't need a slot!"); 0
1243 ----
1244 unsigned DestSlot = fNext++; 0
1245 fMap[V] = DestSlot; 0
1246 ----
1247 // G = Global, F = Function, o = other ----
1248 ST_DEBUG(" Inserting value [" << V->getType() << "] = " << V << " slot=" << ----
1249 DestSlot << " [o]\n"); ----
1250 } 0
1251 ----
1252 /// CreateModuleSlot - Insert the specified MDNode* into the slot table. ----
1253 void SlotTracker::CreateMetadataSlot(const MDNode *N) { 0
1254 assert(N && "Can't insert a null Value into SlotTracker!"); 0
1255 ----
1256 // Don't make slots for DIExpressions or DIArgLists. We just print them inline ----
1257 // everywhere. ----
1258 if (isa(N) || isa(N)) 0
1259 return; 0
1260 ----
1261 unsigned DestSlot = mdnNext; 0
1262 if (!mdnMap.insert(std::make_pair(N, DestSlot)).second) 0
1263 return; 0
1264 ++mdnNext; 0
1265 ----
1266 // Recursively add any MDNodes referenced by operands. ----
1267 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
1268 if (const MDNode *Op = dyn_cast_or_null(N->getOperand(i))) 0
1269 CreateMetadataSlot(Op); 0
1270 } ----
1271 ----
1272 void SlotTracker::CreateAttributeSetSlot(AttributeSet AS) { 0
1273 assert(AS.hasAttributes() && "Doesn't need a slot!"); 0
1274 ----
1275 as_iterator I = asMap.find(AS); 0
1276 if (I != asMap.end()) 0
1277 return; 0
1278 ----
1279 unsigned DestSlot = asNext++; 0
1280 asMap[AS] = DestSlot; 0
1281 } ----
1282 ----
1283 /// Create a new slot for the specified Module ----
1284 void SlotTracker::CreateModulePathSlot(StringRef Path) { 0
1285 ModulePathMap[Path] = ModulePathNext++; 0
1286 } 0
1287 ----
1288 /// Create a new slot for the specified GUID ----
1289 void SlotTracker::CreateGUIDSlot(GlobalValue::GUID GUID) { 0
1290 GUIDMap[GUID] = GUIDNext++; 0
1291 } 0
1292 ----
1293 /// Create a new slot for the specified Id ----
1294 void SlotTracker::CreateTypeIdSlot(StringRef Id) { 0
1295 TypeIdMap[Id] = TypeIdNext++; 0
1296 } 0

1305 AsmWriterContext(TypePrinting *TP, SlotTracker *ST, const Module *M = nullptr) 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1306 : TypePrinter(TP), Machine(ST), Context(M) {} 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

1325 static void WriteAsOperandInternal(raw_ostream &Out, const Value *V, ----
1326 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx); ----

1329 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx, ----
1330 bool FromValue = false); ----
1331 ----
1332 static void WriteOptimizationInfo(raw_ostream &Out, const User *U) { 0
1333 if (const FPMathOperator *FPO = dyn_cast(U)) 0
1334 Out << FPO->getFastMathFlags(); 0
1335 ----
1336 if (const OverflowingBinaryOperator *OBO = 0
1337 dyn_cast(U)) { 0
1338 if (OBO->hasNoUnsignedWrap()) 0
1339 Out << " nuw"; 0
1340 if (OBO->hasNoSignedWrap()) 0
1341 Out << " nsw"; 0
1342 } else if (const PossiblyExactOperator *Div = 0
1343 dyn_cast(U)) { 0
1344 if (Div->isExact()) 0
1345 Out << " exact"; 0
1346 } else if (const GEPOperator *GEP = dyn_cast(U)) { 0
1347 if (GEP->isInBounds()) 0
1348 Out << " inbounds"; 0
1349 } ----
1350 } 0
1351 ----
1352 static void WriteConstantInternal(raw_ostream &Out, const Constant *CV, 0
1353 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) { ----
1354 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1355 if (CI->getType()->isIntegerTy(1)) { 0
1356 Out << (CI->getZExtValue() ? "true" : "false"); 0
1357 return; 0
1358 } ----
1359 Out << CI->getValue(); 0
1360 return; 0
1361 } ----
1362 ----
1363 if (const ConstantFP *CFP = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1364 const APFloat &APF = CFP->getValueAPF(); 0
1365 if (&APF.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEsingle() || 0
1366 &APF.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEdouble()) { 0
1367 // We would like to output the FP constant value in exponential notation, ----
1368 // but we cannot do this if doing so will lose precision. Check here to ----
1369 // make sure that we only output it in exponential format if we can parse ----
1370 // the value back and get the same value. ----
1371 // ----
1372 bool ignored; ----
1373 bool isDouble = &APF.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEdouble(); 0
1374 bool isInf = APF.isInfinity(); 0
1375 bool isNaN = APF.isNaN(); 0
1376 if (!isInf && !isNaN) { 0
1377 double Val = APF.convertToDouble(); 0
1378 SmallString<128> StrVal; 0
1379 APF.toString(StrVal, 6, 0, false); 0
1380 // Check to make sure that the stringized number is not some string like ----
1381 // "Inf" or NaN, that atof will accept, but the lexer will not. Check ----
1382 // that the string matches the "[-+]?[0-9]" regex. ----
1383 // ----
1384 assert((isDigit(StrVal[0]) || ((StrVal[0] == '-' || StrVal[0] == '+') && 0
1385 isDigit(StrVal[1]))) && ----
1386 "[-+]?[0-9] regex does not match!"); ----
1387 // Reparse stringized version! ----
1388 if (APFloat(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), StrVal).convertToDouble() == Val) { 0
1389 Out << StrVal; 0
1390 return; 0
1391 } ----
1392 } 0
1393 // Otherwise we could not reparse it to exactly the same value, so we must ----
1394 // output the string in hexadecimal format! Note that loading and storing ----
1395 // floating point types changes the bits of NaNs on some hosts, notably ----
1396 // x86, so we must not use these types. ----
1397 static_assert(sizeof(double) == sizeof(uint64_t), ----
1398 "assuming that double is 64 bits!"); ----
1399 APFloat apf = APF; 0
1400 // Floats are represented in ASCII IR as double, convert. ----
1401 // FIXME: We should allow 32-bit hex float and remove this. ----
1402 if (!isDouble) { 0
1403 // A signaling NaN is quieted on conversion, so we need to recreate the ----
1404 // expected value after convert (quiet bit of the payload is clear). ----
1405 bool IsSNAN = apf.isSignaling(); 0
1406 apf.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, 0
1407 &ignored); ----
1408 if (IsSNAN) { 0
1409 APInt Payload = apf.bitcastToAPInt(); 0
1410 apf = APFloat::getSNaN(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), apf.isNegative(), 0
1411 &Payload); 0
1412 } 0
1413 } ----
1414 Out << format_hex(apf.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), 0, /*Upper=*/true); 0
1415 return; 0
1416 } 0
1417 ----
1418 // Either half, bfloat or some form of long double. ----
1419 // These appear as a magic letter identifying the type, then a ----
1420 // fixed number of hex digits. ----
1421 Out << "0x"; 0
1422 APInt API = APF.bitcastToAPInt(); 0
1423 if (&APF.getSemantics() == &APFloat::x87DoubleExtended()) { 0
1424 Out << 'K'; 0
1425 Out << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getHiBits(16).getZExtValue(), 4, 0
1426 /*Upper=*/true); 0
1427 Out << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getLoBits(64).getZExtValue(), 16, 0
1428 /*Upper=*/true); 0
1429 return; 0
1430 } else if (&APF.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEquad()) { 0
1431 Out << 'L'; 0
1432 Out << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getLoBits(64).getZExtValue(), 16, 0
1433 /*Upper=*/true); 0
1434 Out << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getHiBits(64).getZExtValue(), 16, 0
1435 /*Upper=*/true); 0
1436 } else if (&APF.getSemantics() == &APFloat::PPCDoubleDouble()) { 0
1437 Out << 'M'; 0
1438 Out << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getLoBits(64).getZExtValue(), 16, 0
1439 /*Upper=*/true); 0
1440 Out << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getHiBits(64).getZExtValue(), 16, 0
1441 /*Upper=*/true); 0
1442 } else if (&APF.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEhalf()) { 0
1443 Out << 'H'; 0
1444 Out << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getZExtValue(), 4, 0
1445 /*Upper=*/true); 0
1446 } else if (&APF.getSemantics() == &APFloat::BFloat()) { 0
1447 Out << 'R'; 0
1448 Out << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getZExtValue(), 4, 0
1449 /*Upper=*/true); 0
1450 } else ----
1451 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported floating point type"); 0
1452 return; 0
1453 } 0
1454 ----
1455 if (isa(CV) || isa(CV)) { 0
1456 Out << "zeroinitializer"; 0
1457 return; 0
1458 } ----
1459 ----
1460 if (const BlockAddress *BA = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1461 Out << "blockaddress("; 0
1462 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, BA->getFunction(), WriterCtx); 0
1463 Out << ", "; 0
1464 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, BA->getBasicBlock(), WriterCtx); 0
1465 Out << ")"; 0
1466 return; 0
1467 } ----
1468 ----
1469 if (const auto *Equiv = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1470 Out << "dso_local_equivalent "; 0
1471 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, Equiv->getGlobalValue(), WriterCtx); 0
1472 return; 0
1473 } ----
1474 ----
1475 if (const auto *NC = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1476 Out << "no_cfi "; 0
1477 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, NC->getGlobalValue(), WriterCtx); 0
1478 return; 0
1479 } ----
1480 ----
1481 if (const ConstantArray *CA = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1482 Type *ETy = CA->getType()->getElementType(); 0
1483 Out << '['; 0
1484 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(ETy, Out); 0
1485 Out << ' '; 0
1486 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, CA->getOperand(0), WriterCtx); 0
1487 for (unsigned i = 1, e = CA->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1488 Out << ", "; 0
1489 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(ETy, Out); 0
1490 Out << ' '; 0
1491 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, CA->getOperand(i), WriterCtx); 0
1492 } ----
1493 Out << ']'; 0
1494 return; 0
1495 } ----
1496 ----
1497 if (const ConstantDataArray *CA = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1498 // As a special case, print the array as a string if it is an array of ----
1499 // i8 with ConstantInt values. ----
1500 if (CA->isString()) { 0
1501 Out << "c\""; 0
1502 printEscapedString(CA->getAsString(), Out); 0
1503 Out << '"'; 0
1504 return; 0
1505 } ----
1506 ----
1507 Type *ETy = CA->getType()->getElementType(); 0
1508 Out << '['; 0
1509 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(ETy, Out); 0
1510 Out << ' '; 0
1511 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, CA->getElementAsConstant(0), WriterCtx); 0
1512 for (unsigned i = 1, e = CA->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1513 Out << ", "; 0
1514 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(ETy, Out); 0
1515 Out << ' '; 0
1516 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, CA->getElementAsConstant(i), WriterCtx); 0
1517 } ----
1518 Out << ']'; 0
1519 return; 0
1520 } ----
1521 ----
1522 if (const ConstantStruct *CS = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1523 if (CS->getType()->isPacked()) 0
1524 Out << '<'; 0
1525 Out << '{'; 0
1526 unsigned N = CS->getNumOperands(); 0
1527 if (N) { 0
1528 Out << ' '; 0
1529 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(CS->getOperand(0)->getType(), Out); 0
1530 Out << ' '; 0
1531 ----
1532 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, CS->getOperand(0), WriterCtx); 0
1533 ----
1534 for (unsigned i = 1; i < N; i++) { 0
1535 Out << ", "; 0
1536 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(CS->getOperand(i)->getType(), Out); 0
1537 Out << ' '; 0
1538 ----
1539 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, CS->getOperand(i), WriterCtx); 0
1540 } ----
1541 Out << ' '; 0
1542 } ----
1543 ----
1544 Out << '}'; 0
1545 if (CS->getType()->isPacked()) 0
1546 Out << '>'; 0
1547 return; 0
1548 } ----
1549 ----
1550 if (isa(CV) || isa(CV)) { 0
1551 auto *CVVTy = cast(CV->getType()); 0
1552 Type *ETy = CVVTy->getElementType(); 0
1553 Out << '<'; 0
1554 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(ETy, Out); 0
1555 Out << ' '; 0
1556 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, CV->getAggregateElement(0U), WriterCtx); 0
1557 for (unsigned i = 1, e = CVVTy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1558 Out << ", "; 0
1559 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(ETy, Out); 0
1560 Out << ' '; 0
1561 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, CV->getAggregateElement(i), WriterCtx); 0
1562 } ----
1563 Out << '>'; 0
1564 return; 0
1565 } ----
1566 ----
1567 if (isa(CV)) { 0
1568 Out << "null"; 0
1569 return; 0
1570 } ----
1571 ----
1572 if (isa(CV)) { 0
1573 Out << "none"; 0
1574 return; 0
1575 } ----
1576 ----
1577 if (isa(CV)) { 0
1578 Out << "poison"; 0
1579 return; 0
1580 } ----
1581 ----
1582 if (isa(CV)) { 0
1583 Out << "undef"; 0
1584 return; 0
1585 } ----
1586 ----
1587 if (const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1588 Out << CE->getOpcodeName(); 0
1589 WriteOptimizationInfo(Out, CE); 0
1590 if (CE->isCompare()) 0
1591 Out << ' ' << static_cast(CE->getPredicate()); 0
1592 Out << " ("; 0
1593 ----
1594 std::optional InRangeOp; 0
1595 if (const GEPOperator *GEP = dyn_cast(CE)) { 0
1596 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(GEP->getSourceElementType(), Out); 0
1597 Out << ", "; 0
1598 InRangeOp = GEP->getInRangeIndex(); 0
1599 if (InRangeOp) 0
1600 ++*InRangeOp; 0
1601 } ----
1602 ----
1603 for (User::const_op_iterator OI=CE->op_begin(); OI != CE->op_end(); ++OI) { 0
1604 if (InRangeOp && unsigned(OI - CE->op_begin()) == *InRangeOp) 0
1605 Out << "inrange "; 0
1606 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print((*OI)->getType(), Out); 0
1607 Out << ' '; 0
1608 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, *OI, WriterCtx); 0
1609 if (OI+1 != CE->op_end()) 0
1610 Out << ", "; 0
1611 } ----
1612 ----
1613 if (CE->isCast()) { 0
1614 Out << " to "; 0
1615 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(CE->getType(), Out); 0
1616 } ----
1617 ----
1618 if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::ShuffleVector) 0
1619 PrintShuffleMask(Out, CE->getType(), CE->getShuffleMask()); 0
1620 ----
1621 Out << ')'; 0
1622 return; 0
1623 } ----
1624 ----
1625 Out << ""; 0
1626 } ----
1627 ----
1628 static void writeMDTuple(raw_ostream &Out, const MDTuple *Node, 0
1629 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) { ----
1630 Out << "!{"; 0
1631 for (unsigned mi = 0, me = Node->getNumOperands(); mi != me; ++mi) { 0
1632 const Metadata *MD = Node->getOperand(mi); 0
1633 if (!MD) 0
1634 Out << "null"; 0
1635 else if (auto *MDV = dyn_cast(MD)) { 0
1636 Value *V = MDV->getValue(); 0
1637 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(V->getType(), Out); 0
1638 Out << ' '; 0
1639 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, V, WriterCtx); 0
1640 } else { ----
1641 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, MD, WriterCtx); 0
1642 WriterCtx.onWriteMetadataAsOperand(MD); 0
1643 } ----
1644 if (mi + 1 != me) 0
1645 Out << ", "; 0
1646 } ----
1647 ----
1648 Out << "}"; 0
1649 } 0

1653 struct FieldSeparator { ----
1654 bool Skip = true; ----
1655 const char *Sep; ----
1656 ----
1657 FieldSeparator(const char *Sep = ", ") : Sep(Sep) {} 0
1658 }; ----
1659 ----
1660 raw_ostream &operator<<(raw_ostream &OS, FieldSeparator &FS) { 0
1661 if (FS.Skip) { 0
1662 FS.Skip = false; 0
1663 return OS; 0
1664 } ----
1665 return OS << FS.Sep; 0
1666 } ----

1780 void MDFieldPrinter::printDIFlags(StringRef Name, DINode::DIFlags Flags) { 0
1781 if (!Flags) 0
1782 return; 0
1783 ----
1784 Out << FS << Name << ": "; 0
1785 ----
1786 SmallVector SplitFlags; 0
1787 auto Extra = DINode::splitFlags(Flags, SplitFlags); 0
1788 ----
1789 FieldSeparator FlagsFS(" | "); 0
1790 for (auto F : SplitFlags) { 0
1791 auto StringF = DINode::getFlagString(F); 0
1792 assert(!StringF.empty() && "Expected valid flag"); 0
1793 Out << FlagsFS << StringF; 0
1794 } ----
1795 if (Extra || SplitFlags.empty()) 0
1796 Out << FlagsFS << Extra; 0
1797 } 0
1798 ----
1799 void MDFieldPrinter::printDISPFlags(StringRef Name, 0
1800 DISubprogram::DISPFlags Flags) { ----
1801 // Always print this field, because no flags in the IR at all will be ----
1802 // interpreted as old-style isDefinition: true. ----
1803 Out << FS << Name << ": "; 0
1804 ----
1805 if (!Flags) { 0
1806 Out << 0; 0
1807 return; 0
1808 } ----
1809 ----
1810 SmallVector SplitFlags; 0
1811 auto Extra = DISubprogram::splitFlags(Flags, SplitFlags); 0
1812 ----
1813 FieldSeparator FlagsFS(" | "); 0
1814 for (auto F : SplitFlags) { 0
1815 auto StringF = DISubprogram::getFlagString(F); 0
1816 assert(!StringF.empty() && "Expected valid flag"); 0
1817 Out << FlagsFS << StringF; 0
1818 } ----
1819 if (Extra || SplitFlags.empty()) 0
1820 Out << FlagsFS << Extra; 0
1821 } 0

1849 static void writeGenericDINode(raw_ostream &Out, const GenericDINode *N, 0
1850 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) { ----
1851 Out << "!GenericDINode("; 0
1852 MDFieldPrinter Printer(Out, WriterCtx); 0
1853 Printer.printTag(N); 0
1854 Printer.printString("header", N->getHeader()); 0
1855 if (N->getNumDwarfOperands()) { 0
1856 Out << Printer.FS << "operands: {"; 0
1857 FieldSeparator IFS; 0
1858 for (auto &I : N->dwarf_operands()) { 0
1859 Out << IFS; 0
1860 writeMetadataAsOperand(Out, I, WriterCtx); 0
1861 } ----
1862 Out << "}"; 0
1863 } ----
1864 Out << ")"; 0
1865 } 0

1887 static void writeDISubrange(raw_ostream &Out, const DISubrange *N, 0
1888 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) { ----
1889 Out << "!DISubrange("; 0
1890 MDFieldPrinter Printer(Out, WriterCtx); 0
1891 ----
1892 auto *Count = N->getRawCountNode(); 0
1893 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast_or_null(Count)) { 0
1894 auto *CV = cast(CE->getValue()); 0
1895 Printer.printInt("count", CV->getSExtValue(), 0
1896 /* ShouldSkipZero */ false); ----
1897 } else ----
1898 Printer.printMetadata("count", Count, /*ShouldSkipNull */ true); 0
1899 ----
1900 // A lowerBound of constant 0 should not be skipped, since it is different ----
1901 // from an unspecified lower bound (= nullptr). ----
1902 auto *LBound = N->getRawLowerBound(); 0
1903 if (auto *LE = dyn_cast_or_null(LBound)) { 0
1904 auto *LV = cast(LE->getValue()); 0
1905 Printer.printInt("lowerBound", LV->getSExtValue(), 0
1906 /* ShouldSkipZero */ false); ----
1907 } else ----
1908 Printer.printMetadata("lowerBound", LBound, /*ShouldSkipNull */ true); 0
1909 ----
1910 auto *UBound = N->getRawUpperBound(); 0
1911 if (auto *UE = dyn_cast_or_null(UBound)) { 0
1912 auto *UV = cast(UE->getValue()); 0
1913 Printer.printInt("upperBound", UV->getSExtValue(), 0
1914 /* ShouldSkipZero */ false); ----
1915 } else ----
1916 Printer.printMetadata("upperBound", UBound, /*ShouldSkipNull */ true); 0
1917 ----
1918 auto *Stride = N->getRawStride(); 0
1919 if (auto *SE = dyn_cast_or_null(Stride)) { 0
1920 auto *SV = cast(SE->getValue()); 0
1921 Printer.printInt("stride", SV->getSExtValue(), /* ShouldSkipZero */ false); 0
1922 } else ----
1923 Printer.printMetadata("stride", Stride, /*ShouldSkipNull */ true); 0
1924 ----
1925 Out << ")"; 0
1926 } 0
1927 ----
1928 static void writeDIGenericSubrange(raw_ostream &Out, const DIGenericSubrange *N, 0
1929 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) { ----
1930 Out << "!DIGenericSubrange("; 0
1931 MDFieldPrinter Printer(Out, WriterCtx); 0
1932 ----
1933 auto IsConstant = [&](Metadata *Bound) -> bool { 0
1934 if (auto *BE = dyn_cast_or_null(Bound)) { 0
1935 return BE->isConstant() && 0
1936 DIExpression::SignedOrUnsignedConstant::SignedConstant == ----
1937 *BE->isConstant(); 0
1938 } ----
1939 return false; 0
1940 }; ----
1941 ----
1942 auto GetConstant = [&](Metadata *Bound) -> int64_t { 0
1943 assert(IsConstant(Bound) && "Expected constant"); 0
1944 auto *BE = dyn_cast_or_null(Bound); 0
1945 return static_cast(BE->getElement(1)); 0
1946 }; 0
1947 ----
1948 auto *Count = N->getRawCountNode(); 0
1949 if (IsConstant(Count)) 0
1950 Printer.printInt("count", GetConstant(Count), 0
1951 /* ShouldSkipZero */ false); ----
1952 else ----
1953 Printer.printMetadata("count", Count, /*ShouldSkipNull */ true); 0
1954 ----
1955 auto *LBound = N->getRawLowerBound(); 0
1956 if (IsConstant(LBound)) 0
1957 Printer.printInt("lowerBound", GetConstant(LBound), 0
1958 /* ShouldSkipZero */ false); ----
1959 else ----
1960 Printer.printMetadata("lowerBound", LBound, /*ShouldSkipNull */ true); 0
1961 ----
1962 auto *UBound = N->getRawUpperBound(); 0
1963 if (IsConstant(UBound)) 0
1964 Printer.printInt("upperBound", GetConstant(UBound), 0
1965 /* ShouldSkipZero */ false); ----
1966 else ----
1967 Printer.printMetadata("upperBound", UBound, /*ShouldSkipNull */ true); 0
1968 ----
1969 auto *Stride = N->getRawStride(); 0
1970 if (IsConstant(Stride)) 0
1971 Printer.printInt("stride", GetConstant(Stride), 0
1972 /* ShouldSkipZero */ false); ----
1973 else ----
1974 Printer.printMetadata("stride", Stride, /*ShouldSkipNull */ true); 0
1975 ----
1976 Out << ")"; 0
1977 } 0

2316 static void writeDIExpression(raw_ostream &Out, const DIExpression *N, 0
2317 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) { ----
2318 Out << "!DIExpression("; 0
2319 FieldSeparator FS; 0
2320 if (N->isValid()) { 0
2321 for (const DIExpression::ExprOperand &Op : N->expr_ops()) { 0
2322 auto OpStr = dwarf::OperationEncodingString(Op.getOp()); 0
2323 assert(!OpStr.empty() && "Expected valid opcode"); 0
2324 ----
2325 Out << FS << OpStr; 0
2326 if (Op.getOp() == dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_convert) { 0
2327 Out << FS << Op.getArg(0); 0
2328 Out << FS << dwarf::AttributeEncodingString(Op.getArg(1)); 0
2329 } else { ----
2330 for (unsigned A = 0, AE = Op.getNumArgs(); A != AE; ++A) 0
2331 Out << FS << Op.getArg(A); 0
2332 } ----
2333 } ----
2334 } else { ----
2335 for (const auto &I : N->getElements()) 0
2336 Out << FS << I; 0
2337 } ----
2338 Out << ")"; 0
2339 } 0

2341 static void writeDIArgList(raw_ostream &Out, const DIArgList *N, 0
2342 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx, ----
2343 bool FromValue = false) { ----
2344 assert(FromValue && 0
2345 "Unexpected DIArgList metadata outside of value argument"); ----
2346 Out << "!DIArgList("; 0
2347 FieldSeparator FS; 0
2348 MDFieldPrinter Printer(Out, WriterCtx); 0
2349 for (Metadata *Arg : N->getArgs()) { 0
2350 Out << FS; 0
2351 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, Arg, WriterCtx, true); 0
2352 } ----
2353 Out << ")"; 0
2354 } 0

2375 Printer.printInt("attributes", N->getAttributes()); 0
2376 Printer.printMetadata("type", N->getRawType()); 0
2377 Out << ")"; 0
2378 } 0
2379 ----
2380 static void writeDIImportedEntity(raw_ostream &Out, const DIImportedEntity *N, 0
2381 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) { ----
2382 Out << "!DIImportedEntity("; 0
2383 MDFieldPrinter Printer(Out, WriterCtx); 0
2384 Printer.printTag(N); 0
2385 Printer.printString("name", N->getName()); 0
2386 Printer.printMetadata("scope", N->getRawScope(), /* ShouldSkipNull */ false); 0
2387 Printer.printMetadata("entity", N->getRawEntity()); 0
2388 Printer.printMetadata("file", N->getRawFile()); 0
2389 Printer.printInt("line", N->getLine()); 0
2390 Printer.printMetadata("elements", N->getRawElements()); 0
2391 Out << ")"; 0
2392 } 0
2393 ----
2394 static void WriteMDNodeBodyInternal(raw_ostream &Out, const MDNode *Node, 0
2395 AsmWriterContext &Ctx) { ----
2396 if (Node->isDistinct()) 0
2397 Out << "distinct "; 0
2398 else if (Node->isTemporary()) 0
2399 Out << " "; // Handle broken code. 0
2400 ----
2401 switch (Node->getMetadataID()) { 0
2402 default: 0
2403 llvm_unreachable("Expected uniquable MDNode"); 0
2404 #define HANDLE_MDNODE_LEAF(CLASS) \ ----
2405 case Metadata::CLASS##Kind: \ ----
2406 write##CLASS(Out, cast(Node), Ctx); \ ----
2407 break; ----
2408 #include "llvm/IR/Metadata.def" ----
2409 } ----
2410 } 0
2411 ----
2412 // Full implementation of printing a Value as an operand with support for ----
2413 // TypePrinting, etc. ----
2414 static void WriteAsOperandInternal(raw_ostream &Out, const Value *V, 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2415 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx) { ----
2416 if (V->hasName()) { 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2417 PrintLLVMName(Out, V); 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2418 return; 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2419 } ----
2420 ----
2421 const Constant *CV = dyn_cast(V); 0
2422 if (CV && !isa(CV)) { 0
2423 assert(WriterCtx.TypePrinter && "Constants require TypePrinting!"); 0
2424 WriteConstantInternal(Out, CV, WriterCtx); 0
2425 return; 0
2426 } ----
2427 ----
2428 if (const InlineAsm *IA = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
2429 Out << "asm "; 0
2430 if (IA->hasSideEffects()) 0
2431 Out << "sideeffect "; 0
2432 if (IA->isAlignStack()) 0
2433 Out << "alignstack "; 0
2434 // We don't emit the AD_ATT dialect as it's the assumed default. ----
2435 if (IA->getDialect() == InlineAsm::AD_Intel) 0
2436 Out << "inteldialect "; 0
2437 if (IA->canThrow()) 0
2438 Out << "unwind "; 0
2439 Out << '"'; 0
2440 printEscapedString(IA->getAsmString(), Out); 0
2441 Out << "\", \""; 0
2442 printEscapedString(IA->getConstraintString(), Out); 0
2443 Out << '"'; 0
2444 return; 0
2445 } ----
2446 ----
2447 if (auto *MD = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
2448 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, MD->getMetadata(), WriterCtx, 0
2449 /* FromValue */ true); ----
2450 return; 0
2451 } ----
2452 ----
2453 char Prefix = '%'; 0
2454 int Slot; ----
2455 auto *Machine = WriterCtx.Machine; 0
2456 // If we have a SlotTracker, use it. ----
2457 if (Machine) { 0
2458 if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
2459 Slot = Machine->getGlobalSlot(GV); 0
2460 Prefix = '@'; 0
2461 } else { ----
2462 Slot = Machine->getLocalSlot(V); 0
2463 ----
2464 // If the local value didn't succeed, then we may be referring to a value ----
2465 // from a different function. Translate it, as this can happen when using ----
2466 // address of blocks. ----
2467 if (Slot == -1) 0
2468 if ((Machine = createSlotTracker(V))) { 0
2469 Slot = Machine->getLocalSlot(V); 0
2470 delete Machine; 0
2471 } ----
2472 } ----
2473 } else if ((Machine = createSlotTracker(V))) { 0
2474 // Otherwise, create one to get the # and then destroy it. ----
2475 if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
2476 Slot = Machine->getGlobalSlot(GV); 0
2477 Prefix = '@'; 0
2478 } else { ----
2479 Slot = Machine->getLocalSlot(V); 0
2480 } ----
2481 delete Machine; 0
2482 Machine = nullptr; 0
2483 } else { ----
2484 Slot = -1; 0
2485 } ----
2486 ----
2487 if (Slot != -1) 0
2488 Out << Prefix << Slot; 0
2489 else ----
2490 Out << ""; 0
2491 } ----
2492 ----
2493 static void WriteAsOperandInternal(raw_ostream &Out, const Metadata *MD, 0
2494 AsmWriterContext &WriterCtx, ----
2495 bool FromValue) { ----
2496 // Write DIExpressions and DIArgLists inline when used as a value. Improves ----
2497 // readability of debug info intrinsics. ----
2498 if (const DIExpression *Expr = dyn_cast(MD)) { 0
2499 writeDIExpression(Out, Expr, WriterCtx); 0
2500 return; 0
2501 } ----
2502 if (const DIArgList *ArgList = dyn_cast(MD)) { 0
2503 writeDIArgList(Out, ArgList, WriterCtx, FromValue); 0
2504 return; 0
2505 } ----
2506 ----
2507 if (const MDNode *N = dyn_cast(MD)) { 0
2508 std::unique_ptr MachineStorage; 0
2509 SaveAndRestore SARMachine(WriterCtx.Machine); 0
2510 if (!WriterCtx.Machine) { 0
2511 MachineStorage = std::make_unique(WriterCtx.Context); 0
2512 WriterCtx.Machine = MachineStorage.get(); 0
2513 } ----
2514 int Slot = WriterCtx.Machine->getMetadataSlot(N); 0
2515 if (Slot == -1) { 0
2516 if (const DILocation *Loc = dyn_cast(N)) { 0
2517 writeDILocation(Out, Loc, WriterCtx); 0
2518 return; 0
2519 } ----
2520 // Give the pointer value instead of "badref", since this comes up all ----
2521 // the time when debugging. ----
2522 Out << "<" << N << ">"; 0
2523 } else ----
2524 Out << '!' << Slot; 0
2525 return; 0
2526 } 0
2527 ----
2528 if (const MDString *MDS = dyn_cast(MD)) { 0
2529 Out << "!\""; 0
2530 printEscapedString(MDS->getString(), Out); 0
2531 Out << '"'; 0
2532 return; 0
2533 } ----
2534 ----
2535 auto *V = cast(MD); 0
2536 assert(WriterCtx.TypePrinter && "TypePrinter required for metadata values"); 0
2537 assert((FromValue || !isa(V)) && 0
2538 "Unexpected function-local metadata outside of value argument"); ----
2539 ----
2540 WriterCtx.TypePrinter->print(V->getValue()->getType(), Out); 0
2541 Out << ' '; 0
2542 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, V->getValue(), WriterCtx); 0
2543 } ----

2680 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, Operand, WriterCtx); 0
2681 } 0

2685 switch (SSID) { 0
2686 case SyncScope::System: { 0
2687 break; 0
2688 } ----
2689 default: { 0
2690 if (SSNs.empty()) 0
2691 Context.getSyncScopeNames(SSNs); 0
2692 ----
2693 Out << " syncscope(\""; 0
2694 printEscapedString(SSNs[SSID], Out); 0
2695 Out << "\")"; 0
2696 break; 0
2697 } ----
2698 } ----
2699 } 0

2723 void AssemblyWriter::writeParamOperand(const Value *Operand, 0
2724 AttributeSet Attrs) { ----
2725 if (!Operand) { 0
2726 Out << ""; 0
2727 return; 0
2728 } ----
2729 ----
2730 // Print the type ----
2731 TypePrinter.print(Operand->getType(), Out); 0
2732 // Print parameter attributes list ----
2733 if (Attrs.hasAttributes()) { 0
2734 Out << ' '; 0
2735 writeAttributeSet(Attrs); 0
2736 } ----
2737 Out << ' '; 0
2738 // Print the operand ----
2739 auto WriterCtx = getContext(); 0
2740 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, Operand, WriterCtx); 0
2741 } 0
2742 ----
2743 void AssemblyWriter::writeOperandBundles(const CallBase *Call) { 0
2744 if (!Call->hasOperandBundles()) 0
2745 return; 0
2746 ----
2747 Out << " [ "; 0
2748 ----
2749 bool FirstBundle = true; 0
2750 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Call->getNumOperandBundles(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2751 OperandBundleUse BU = Call->getOperandBundleAt(i); 0
2752 ----
2753 if (!FirstBundle) 0
2754 Out << ", "; 0
2755 FirstBundle = false; 0
2756 ----
2757 Out << '"'; 0
2758 printEscapedString(BU.getTagName(), Out); 0
2759 Out << '"'; 0
2760 ----
2761 Out << '('; 0
2762 ----
2763 bool FirstInput = true; 0
2764 auto WriterCtx = getContext(); 0
2765 for (const auto &Input : BU.Inputs) { 0
2766 if (!FirstInput) 0
2767 Out << ", "; 0
2768 FirstInput = false; 0
2769 ----
2770 if (Input == nullptr) 0
2771 Out << ""; 0
2772 else { ----
2773 TypePrinter.print(Input->getType(), Out); 0
2774 Out << " "; 0
2775 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, Input, WriterCtx); 0
2776 } ----
2777 } ----
2778 ----
2779 Out << ')'; 0
2780 } 0
2781 ----
2782 Out << " ]"; 0
2783 } ----
2784 ----
2785 void AssemblyWriter::printModule(const Module *M) { 0
2786 Machine.initializeIfNeeded(); 0
2787 ----
2788 if (ShouldPreserveUseListOrder) 0
2789 UseListOrders = predictUseListOrder(M); 0
2790 ----
2791 if (!M->getModuleIdentifier().empty() && 0
2792 // Don't print the ID if it will start a new line (which would ----
2793 // require a comment char before it). ----
2794 M->getModuleIdentifier().find('\n') == std::string::npos) 0
2795 Out << "; ModuleID = '" << M->getModuleIdentifier() << "'\n"; 0
2796 ----
2797 if (!M->getSourceFileName().empty()) { 0
2798 Out << "source_filename = \""; 0
2799 printEscapedString(M->getSourceFileName(), Out); 0
2800 Out << "\"\n"; 0
2801 } ----
2802 ----
2803 const std::string &DL = M->getDataLayoutStr(); 0
2804 if (!DL.empty()) 0
2805 Out << "target datalayout = \"" << DL << "\"\n"; 0
2806 if (!M->getTargetTriple().empty()) 0
2807 Out << "target triple = \"" << M->getTargetTriple() << "\"\n"; 0
2808 ----
2809 if (!M->getModuleInlineAsm().empty()) { 0
2810 Out << '\n'; 0
2811 ----
2812 // Split the string into lines, to make it easier to read the .ll file. ----
2813 StringRef Asm = M->getModuleInlineAsm(); 0
2814 do { ----
2815 StringRef Front; 0
2816 std::tie(Front, Asm) = Asm.split('\n'); 0
2817 ----
2818 // We found a newline, print the portion of the asm string from the ----
2819 // last newline up to this newline. ----
2820 Out << "module asm \""; 0
2821 printEscapedString(Front, Out); 0
2822 Out << "\"\n"; 0
2823 } while (!Asm.empty()); 0
2824 } ----
2825 ----
2826 printTypeIdentities(); 0
2827 ----
2828 // Output all comdats. ----
2829 if (!Comdats.empty()) 0
2830 Out << '\n'; 0
2831 for (const Comdat *C : Comdats) { 0
2832 printComdat(C); 0
2833 if (C != Comdats.back()) 0
2834 Out << '\n'; 0
2835 } ----
2836 ----
2837 // Output all globals. ----
2838 if (!M->global_empty()) Out << '\n'; 0
2839 for (const GlobalVariable &GV : M->globals()) { 0
2840 printGlobal(&GV); Out << '\n'; 0
2841 } ----
2842 ----
2843 // Output all aliases. ----
2844 if (!M->alias_empty()) Out << "\n"; 0
2845 for (const GlobalAlias &GA : M->aliases()) 0
2846 printAlias(&GA); 0
2847 ----
2848 // Output all ifuncs. ----
2849 if (!M->ifunc_empty()) Out << "\n"; 0
2850 for (const GlobalIFunc &GI : M->ifuncs()) 0
2851 printIFunc(&GI); 0
2852 ----
2853 // Output all of the functions. ----
2854 for (const Function &F : *M) { 0
2855 Out << '\n'; 0
2856 printFunction(&F); 0
2857 } ----
2858 ----
2859 // Output global use-lists. ----
2860 printUseLists(nullptr); 0
2861 ----
2862 // Output all attribute groups. ----
2863 if (!Machine.as_empty()) { 0
2864 Out << '\n'; 0
2865 writeAllAttributeGroups(); 0
2866 } ----
2867 ----
2868 // Output named metadata. ----
2869 if (!M->named_metadata_empty()) Out << '\n'; 0
2870 ----
2871 for (const NamedMDNode &Node : M->named_metadata()) 0
2872 printNamedMDNode(&Node); 0
2873 ----
2874 // Output metadata. ----
2875 if (!Machine.mdn_empty()) { 0
2876 Out << '\n'; 0
2877 writeAllMDNodes(); 0
2878 } ----
2879 } 0
2880 ----
2881 void AssemblyWriter::printModuleSummaryIndex() { 0
2882 assert(TheIndex); 0
2883 int NumSlots = Machine.initializeIndexIfNeeded(); 0
2884 ----
2885 Out << "\n"; 0
2886 ----
2887 // Print module path entries. To print in order, add paths to a vector ----
2888 // indexed by module slot. ----
2889 std::vector> moduleVec; 0
2890 std::string RegularLTOModuleName = ----
2891 ModuleSummaryIndex::getRegularLTOModuleName(); 0
2892 moduleVec.resize(TheIndex->modulePaths().size()); 0
2893 for (auto &[ModPath, ModId] : TheIndex->modulePaths()) 0
2894 moduleVec[Machine.getModulePathSlot(ModPath)] = std::make_pair( 0
2895 // A module id of -1 is a special entry for a regular LTO module created ----
2896 // during the thin link. ----
2897 ModId.first == -1u ? RegularLTOModuleName : std::string(ModPath), 0
2898 ModId.second); 0
2899 ----
2900 unsigned i = 0; 0
2901 for (auto &ModPair : moduleVec) { 0
2902 Out << "^" << i++ << " = module: ("; 0
2903 Out << "path: \""; 0
2904 printEscapedString(ModPair.first, Out); 0
2905 Out << "\", hash: ("; 0
2906 FieldSeparator FS; 0
2907 for (auto Hash : ModPair.second) 0
2908 Out << FS << Hash; 0
2909 Out << "))\n"; 0
2910 } ----
2911 ----
2912 // FIXME: Change AliasSummary to hold a ValueInfo instead of summary pointer ----
2913 // for aliasee (then update BitcodeWriter.cpp and remove get/setAliaseeGUID). ----
2914 for (auto &GlobalList : *TheIndex) { 0
2915 auto GUID = GlobalList.first; 0
2916 for (auto &Summary : GlobalList.second.SummaryList) 0
2917 SummaryToGUIDMap[Summary.get()] = GUID; 0
2918 } ----
2919 ----
2920 // Print the global value summary entries. ----
2921 for (auto &GlobalList : *TheIndex) { 0
2922 auto GUID = GlobalList.first; 0
2923 auto VI = TheIndex->getValueInfo(GlobalList); 0
2924 printSummaryInfo(Machine.getGUIDSlot(GUID), VI); 0
2925 } ----
2926 ----
2927 // Print the TypeIdMap entries. ----
2928 for (const auto &TID : TheIndex->typeIds()) { 0
2929 Out << "^" << Machine.getTypeIdSlot(TID.second.first) 0
2930 << " = typeid: (name: \"" << TID.second.first << "\""; 0
2931 printTypeIdSummary(TID.second.second); 0
2932 Out << ") ; guid = " << TID.first << "\n"; 0
2933 } ----
2934 ----
2935 // Print the TypeIdCompatibleVtableMap entries. ----
2936 for (auto &TId : TheIndex->typeIdCompatibleVtableMap()) { 0
2937 auto GUID = GlobalValue::getGUID(TId.first); 0
2938 Out << "^" << Machine.getGUIDSlot(GUID) 0
2939 << " = typeidCompatibleVTable: (name: \"" << TId.first << "\""; 0
2940 printTypeIdCompatibleVtableSummary(TId.second); 0
2941 Out << ") ; guid = " << GUID << "\n"; 0
2942 } ----
2943 ----
2944 // Don't emit flags when it's not really needed (value is zero by default). ----
2945 if (TheIndex->getFlags()) { 0
2946 Out << "^" << NumSlots << " = flags: " << TheIndex->getFlags() << "\n"; 0
2947 ++NumSlots; 0
2948 } ----
2949 ----
2950 Out << "^" << NumSlots << " = blockcount: " << TheIndex->getBlockCount() 0
2951 << "\n"; 0
2952 } 0

3248 } ----
3249 Out << "))"; 0
3250 } ----
3251 Out << "))"; 0
3252 } ----
3253 Out << ")"; 0
3254 } ----

3263 else ----

3284 }; 0

3300 Out << ", param: " << Call.ParamNo; 0

3470 ----
3471 static void printMetadataIdentifier(StringRef Name, 0
3472 formatted_raw_ostream &Out) { ----
3473 if (Name.empty()) { 0
3474 Out << " "; 0
3475 } else { ----
3476 if (isalpha(static_cast(Name[0])) || Name[0] == '-' || 0
3477 Name[0] == '$' || Name[0] == '.' || Name[0] == '_') 0
3478 Out << Name[0]; 0
3479 else ----
3480 Out << '\\' << hexdigit(Name[0] >> 4) << hexdigit(Name[0] & 0x0F); 0
3481 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Name.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
3482 unsigned char C = Name[i]; 0
3483 if (isalnum(static_cast(C)) || C == '-' || C == '$' || 0
3484 C == '.' || C == '_') 0
3485 Out << C; 0
3486 else ----
3487 Out << '\\' << hexdigit(C >> 4) << hexdigit(C & 0x0F); 0
3488 } ----
3489 } ----
3490 } 0
3491 ----
3492 void AssemblyWriter::printNamedMDNode(const NamedMDNode *NMD) { 0
3493 Out << '!'; 0
3494 printMetadataIdentifier(NMD->getName(), Out); 0
3495 Out << " = !{"; 0
3496 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NMD->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
3497 if (i) 0
3498 Out << ", "; 0
3499 ----
3500 // Write DIExpressions inline. ----
3501 // FIXME: Ban DIExpressions in NamedMDNodes, they will serve no purpose. ----
3502 MDNode *Op = NMD->getOperand(i); 0
3503 assert(!isa(Op) && 0
3504 "DIArgLists should not appear in NamedMDNodes"); ----
3505 if (auto *Expr = dyn_cast(Op)) { 0
3506 writeDIExpression(Out, Expr, AsmWriterContext::getEmpty()); 0
3507 continue; 0
3508 } ----
3509 ----
3510 int Slot = Machine.getMetadataSlot(Op); 0
3511 if (Slot == -1) 0
3512 Out << ""; 0
3513 else ----
3514 Out << '!' << Slot; 0
3515 } ----
3516 Out << "}\n"; 0
3517 } 0

3575 static void maybePrintComdat(formatted_raw_ostream &Out, 0
3576 const GlobalObject &GO) { ----
3577 const Comdat *C = GO.getComdat(); 0
3578 if (!C) 0

3583 Out << " comdat"; 0

3585 if (GO.getName() == C->getName()) 0

3592 ----
3593 void AssemblyWriter::printGlobal(const GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
3594 if (GV->isMaterializable()) 0
3595 Out << "; Materializable\n"; 0
3596 ----
3597 AsmWriterContext WriterCtx(&TypePrinter, &Machine, GV->getParent()); 0
3598 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, GV, WriterCtx); 0
3599 Out << " = "; 0
3600 ----
3601 if (!GV->hasInitializer() && GV->hasExternalLinkage()) 0
3602 Out << "external "; 0
3603 ----
3604 Out << getLinkageNameWithSpace(GV->getLinkage()); 0
3605 PrintDSOLocation(*GV, Out); 0
3606 PrintVisibility(GV->getVisibility(), Out); 0
3607 PrintDLLStorageClass(GV->getDLLStorageClass(), Out); 0
3608 PrintThreadLocalModel(GV->getThreadLocalMode(), Out); 0
3609 StringRef UA = getUnnamedAddrEncoding(GV->getUnnamedAddr()); 0
3610 if (!UA.empty()) 0
3611 Out << UA << ' '; 0
3612 ----
3613 if (unsigned AddressSpace = GV->getType()->getAddressSpace()) 0
3614 Out << "addrspace(" << AddressSpace << ") "; 0
3615 if (GV->isExternallyInitialized()) Out << "externally_initialized "; 0
3616 Out << (GV->isConstant() ? "constant " : "global "); 0
3617 TypePrinter.print(GV->getValueType(), Out); 0
3618 ----
3619 if (GV->hasInitializer()) { 0
3620 Out << ' '; 0
3621 writeOperand(GV->getInitializer(), false); 0
3622 } ----
3623 ----
3624 if (GV->hasSection()) { 0
3625 Out << ", section \""; 0
3626 printEscapedString(GV->getSection(), Out); 0
3627 Out << '"'; 0
3628 } ----
3629 if (GV->hasPartition()) { 0
3630 Out << ", partition \""; 0
3631 printEscapedString(GV->getPartition(), Out); 0
3632 Out << '"'; 0
3633 } ----
3634 ----
3635 using SanitizerMetadata = llvm::GlobalValue::SanitizerMetadata; ----
3636 if (GV->hasSanitizerMetadata()) { 0
3637 SanitizerMetadata MD = GV->getSanitizerMetadata(); 0
3638 if (MD.NoAddress) 0
3639 Out << ", no_sanitize_address"; 0
3640 if (MD.NoHWAddress) 0
3641 Out << ", no_sanitize_hwaddress"; 0
3642 if (MD.Memtag) 0
3643 Out << ", sanitize_memtag"; 0
3644 if (MD.IsDynInit) 0
3645 Out << ", sanitize_address_dyninit"; 0
3646 } ----
3647 ----
3648 maybePrintComdat(Out, *GV); 0
3649 if (MaybeAlign A = GV->getAlign()) 0
3650 Out << ", align " << A->value(); 0
3651 ----
3652 SmallVector, 4> MDs; 0
3653 GV->getAllMetadata(MDs); 0
3654 printMetadataAttachments(MDs, ", "); 0
3655 ----
3656 auto Attrs = GV->getAttributes(); 0
3657 if (Attrs.hasAttributes()) 0
3658 Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(Attrs); 0
3659 ----
3660 printInfoComment(*GV); 0
3661 } 0

3692 if (GA->hasPartition()) { 0
3693 Out << ", partition \""; 0
3694 printEscapedString(GA->getPartition(), Out); 0
3695 Out << '"'; 0
3696 } ----
3697 ----
3698 printInfoComment(*GA); 0
3699 Out << '\n'; 0

3739 ----
3740 void AssemblyWriter::printTypeIdentities() { 0
3741 if (TypePrinter.empty()) 0
3742 return; 0
3743 ----
3744 Out << '\n'; 0
3745 ----
3746 // Emit all numbered types. ----
3747 auto &NumberedTypes = TypePrinter.getNumberedTypes(); 0
3748 for (unsigned I = 0, E = NumberedTypes.size(); I != E; ++I) { 0
3749 Out << '%' << I << " = type "; 0
3750 ----
3751 // Make sure we print out at least one level of the type structure, so ----
3752 // that we do not get %2 = type %2 ----
3753 TypePrinter.printStructBody(NumberedTypes[I], Out); 0
3754 Out << '\n'; 0
3755 } ----
3756 ----
3757 auto &NamedTypes = TypePrinter.getNamedTypes(); 0
3758 for (StructType *NamedType : NamedTypes) { 0
3759 PrintLLVMName(Out, NamedType->getName(), LocalPrefix); 0
3760 Out << " = type "; 0
3761 ----
3762 // Make sure we print out at least one level of the type structure, so ----
3763 // that we do not get %FILE = type %FILE ----
3764 TypePrinter.printStructBody(NamedType, Out); 0
3765 Out << '\n'; 0
3766 } ----
3767 } ----
3768 ----
3769 /// printFunction - Print all aspects of a function. ----
3770 void AssemblyWriter::printFunction(const Function *F) { 0
3771 if (AnnotationWriter) AnnotationWriter->emitFunctionAnnot(F, Out); 0
3772 ----
3773 if (F->isMaterializable()) 0
3774 Out << "; Materializable\n"; 0
3775 ----
3776 const AttributeList &Attrs = F->getAttributes(); 0
3777 if (Attrs.hasFnAttrs()) { 0
3778 AttributeSet AS = Attrs.getFnAttrs(); 0
3779 std::string AttrStr; 0
3780 ----
3781 for (const Attribute &Attr : AS) { 0
3782 if (!Attr.isStringAttribute()) { 0
3783 if (!AttrStr.empty()) AttrStr += ' '; 0
3784 AttrStr += Attr.getAsString(); 0
3785 } ----
3786 } ----
3787 ----
3788 if (!AttrStr.empty()) 0
3789 Out << "; Function Attrs: " << AttrStr << '\n'; 0
3790 } 0
3791 ----
3792 Machine.incorporateFunction(F); 0
3793 ----
3794 if (F->isDeclaration()) { 0
3795 Out << "declare"; 0
3796 SmallVector, 4> MDs; 0
3797 F->getAllMetadata(MDs); 0
3798 printMetadataAttachments(MDs, " "); 0
3799 Out << ' '; 0
3800 } else 0
3801 Out << "define "; 0
3802 ----
3803 Out << getLinkageNameWithSpace(F->getLinkage()); 0
3804 PrintDSOLocation(*F, Out); 0
3805 PrintVisibility(F->getVisibility(), Out); 0
3806 PrintDLLStorageClass(F->getDLLStorageClass(), Out); 0
3807 ----
3808 // Print the calling convention. ----
3809 if (F->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::C) { 0
3810 PrintCallingConv(F->getCallingConv(), Out); 0
3811 Out << " "; 0
3812 } ----
3813 ----
3814 FunctionType *FT = F->getFunctionType(); 0
3815 if (Attrs.hasRetAttrs()) 0
3816 Out << Attrs.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex) << ' '; 0
3817 TypePrinter.print(F->getReturnType(), Out); 0
3818 AsmWriterContext WriterCtx(&TypePrinter, &Machine, F->getParent()); 0
3819 Out << ' '; 0
3820 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, F, WriterCtx); 0
3821 Out << '('; 0
3822 ----
3823 // Loop over the arguments, printing them... ----
3824 if (F->isDeclaration() && !IsForDebug) { 0
3825 // We're only interested in the type here - don't print argument names. ----
3826 for (unsigned I = 0, E = FT->getNumParams(); I != E; ++I) { 0
3827 // Insert commas as we go... the first arg doesn't get a comma ----
3828 if (I) 0
3829 Out << ", "; 0
3830 // Output type... ----
3831 TypePrinter.print(FT->getParamType(I), Out); 0
3832 ----
3833 AttributeSet ArgAttrs = Attrs.getParamAttrs(I); 0
3834 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttributes()) { 0
3835 Out << ' '; 0
3836 writeAttributeSet(ArgAttrs); 0
3837 } ----
3838 } ----
3839 } else { ----
3840 // The arguments are meaningful here, print them in detail. ----
3841 for (const Argument &Arg : F->args()) { 0
3842 // Insert commas as we go... the first arg doesn't get a comma ----
3843 if (Arg.getArgNo() != 0) 0
3844 Out << ", "; 0
3845 printArgument(&Arg, Attrs.getParamAttrs(Arg.getArgNo())); 0
3846 } ----
3847 } ----
3848 ----
3849 // Finish printing arguments... ----
3850 if (FT->isVarArg()) { 0
3851 if (FT->getNumParams()) Out << ", "; 0
3852 Out << "..."; // Output varargs portion of signature! 0
3853 } ----
3854 Out << ')'; 0
3855 StringRef UA = getUnnamedAddrEncoding(F->getUnnamedAddr()); 0
3856 if (!UA.empty()) 0
3857 Out << ' ' << UA; 0
3858 // We print the function address space if it is non-zero or if we are writing ----
3859 // a module with a non-zero program address space or if there is no valid ----
3860 // Module* so that the file can be parsed without the datalayout string. ----
3861 const Module *Mod = F->getParent(); 0
3862 if (F->getAddressSpace() != 0 || !Mod || 0
3863 Mod->getDataLayout().getProgramAddressSpace() != 0) 0
3864 Out << " addrspace(" << F->getAddressSpace() << ")"; 0
3865 if (Attrs.hasFnAttrs()) 0
3866 Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(Attrs.getFnAttrs()); 0
3867 if (F->hasSection()) { 0
3868 Out << " section \""; 0
3869 printEscapedString(F->getSection(), Out); 0
3870 Out << '"'; 0
3871 } ----
3872 if (F->hasPartition()) { 0
3873 Out << " partition \""; 0
3874 printEscapedString(F->getPartition(), Out); 0
3875 Out << '"'; 0
3876 } ----
3877 maybePrintComdat(Out, *F); 0
3878 if (MaybeAlign A = F->getAlign()) 0
3879 Out << " align " << A->value(); 0
3880 if (F->hasGC()) 0
3881 Out << " gc \"" << F->getGC() << '"'; 0
3882 if (F->hasPrefixData()) { 0
3883 Out << " prefix "; 0
3884 writeOperand(F->getPrefixData(), true); 0
3885 } ----
3886 if (F->hasPrologueData()) { 0
3887 Out << " prologue "; 0
3888 writeOperand(F->getPrologueData(), true); 0
3889 } ----
3890 if (F->hasPersonalityFn()) { 0
3891 Out << " personality "; 0
3892 writeOperand(F->getPersonalityFn(), /*PrintType=*/true); 0
3893 } ----
3894 ----
3895 if (F->isDeclaration()) { 0
3896 Out << '\n'; 0
3897 } else { ----
3898 SmallVector, 4> MDs; 0
3899 F->getAllMetadata(MDs); 0
3900 printMetadataAttachments(MDs, " "); 0
3901 ----
3902 Out << " {"; 0
3903 // Output all of the function's basic blocks. ----
3904 for (const BasicBlock &BB : *F) 0
3905 printBasicBlock(&BB); 0
3906 ----
3907 // Output the function's use-lists. ----
3908 printUseLists(F); 0
3909 ----
3910 Out << "}\n"; 0
3911 } 0
3912 ----
3913 Machine.purgeFunction(); 0
3914 } 0
3915 ----
3916 /// printArgument - This member is called for every argument that is passed into ----
3917 /// the function. Simply print it out ----
3918 void AssemblyWriter::printArgument(const Argument *Arg, AttributeSet Attrs) { 0
3919 // Output type... ----
3920 TypePrinter.print(Arg->getType(), Out); 0
3921 ----
3922 // Output parameter attributes list ----
3923 if (Attrs.hasAttributes()) { 0
3924 Out << ' '; 0
3925 writeAttributeSet(Attrs); 0
3926 } ----
3927 ----
3928 // Output name, if available... ----
3929 if (Arg->hasName()) { 0
3930 Out << ' '; 0
3931 PrintLLVMName(Out, Arg); 0
3932 } else { ----
3933 int Slot = Machine.getLocalSlot(Arg); 0
3934 assert(Slot != -1 && "expect argument in function here"); 0
3935 Out << " %" << Slot; 0
3936 } ----
3937 } 0
3938 ----
3939 /// printBasicBlock - This member is called for each basic block in a method. ----
3940 void AssemblyWriter::printBasicBlock(const BasicBlock *BB) { 0
3941 bool IsEntryBlock = BB->getParent() && BB->isEntryBlock(); 0
3942 if (BB->hasName()) { // Print out the label if it exists... 0
3943 Out << "\n"; 0
3944 PrintLLVMName(Out, BB->getName(), LabelPrefix); 0
3945 Out << ':'; 0
3946 } else if (!IsEntryBlock) { 0
3947 Out << "\n"; 0
3948 int Slot = Machine.getLocalSlot(BB); 0
3949 if (Slot != -1) 0
3950 Out << Slot << ":"; 0
3951 else ----
3952 Out << ":"; 0
3953 } ----
3954 ----
3955 if (!IsEntryBlock) { 0
3956 // Output predecessors for the block. ----
3957 Out.PadToColumn(50); 0
3958 Out << ";"; 0
3959 const_pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(BB), PE = pred_end(BB); 0
3960 ----
3961 if (PI == PE) { 0
3962 Out << " No predecessors!"; 0
3963 } else { ----
3964 Out << " preds = "; 0
3965 writeOperand(*PI, false); 0
3966 for (++PI; PI != PE; ++PI) { 0
3967 Out << ", "; 0
3968 writeOperand(*PI, false); 0
3969 } ----
3970 } ----
3971 } ----
3972 ----
3973 Out << "\n"; 0
3974 ----
3975 if (AnnotationWriter) AnnotationWriter->emitBasicBlockStartAnnot(BB, Out); 0
3976 ----
3977 // Output all of the instructions in the basic block... ----
3978 for (const Instruction &I : *BB) { 0
3979 printInstructionLine(I); 0
3980 } ----
3981 ----
3982 if (AnnotationWriter) AnnotationWriter->emitBasicBlockEndAnnot(BB, Out); 0
3983 } 0
3984 ----
3985 /// printInstructionLine - Print an instruction and a newline character. ----
3986 void AssemblyWriter::printInstructionLine(const Instruction &I) { 0
3987 printInstruction(I); 0
3988 Out << '\n'; 0
3989 } 0

4001 /// printInfoComment - Print a little comment after the instruction indicating ----
4002 /// which slot it occupies. ----
4003 void AssemblyWriter::printInfoComment(const Value &V) { 0
4004 if (const auto *Relocate = dyn_cast(&V)) 0
4005 printGCRelocateComment(*Relocate); 0
4006 ----
4007 if (AnnotationWriter) 0
4008 AnnotationWriter->printInfoComment(V, Out); 0
4009 } 0
4010 ----
4011 static void maybePrintCallAddrSpace(const Value *Operand, const Instruction *I, 0
4012 raw_ostream &Out) { ----
4013 // We print the address space of the call if it is non-zero. ----
4014 if (Operand == nullptr) { 0
4015 Out << " "; 0
4016 return; 0
4017 } ----
4018 unsigned CallAddrSpace = Operand->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
4019 bool PrintAddrSpace = CallAddrSpace != 0; 0
4020 if (!PrintAddrSpace) { 0
4021 const Module *Mod = getModuleFromVal(I); 0
4022 // We also print it if it is zero but not equal to the program address space ----
4023 // or if we can't find a valid Module* to make it possible to parse ----
4024 // the resulting file even without a datalayout string. ----
4025 if (!Mod || Mod->getDataLayout().getProgramAddressSpace() != 0) 0
4026 PrintAddrSpace = true; 0
4027 } ----
4028 if (PrintAddrSpace) 0
4029 Out << " addrspace(" << CallAddrSpace << ")"; 0
4030 } ----
4031 ----
4032 // This member is called for each Instruction in a function.. ----
4033 void AssemblyWriter::printInstruction(const Instruction &I) { 0
4034 if (AnnotationWriter) AnnotationWriter->emitInstructionAnnot(&I, Out); 0
4035 ----
4036 // Print out indentation for an instruction. ----
4037 Out << " "; 0
4038 ----
4039 // Print out name if it exists... ----
4040 if (I.hasName()) { 0
4041 PrintLLVMName(Out, &I); 0
4042 Out << " = "; 0
4043 } else if (!I.getType()->isVoidTy()) { 0
4044 // Print out the def slot taken. ----
4045 int SlotNum = Machine.getLocalSlot(&I); 0
4046 if (SlotNum == -1) 0
4047 Out << " = "; 0
4048 else ----
4049 Out << '%' << SlotNum << " = "; 0
4050 } ----
4051 ----
4052 if (const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4053 if (CI->isMustTailCall()) 0
4054 Out << "musttail "; 0
4055 else if (CI->isTailCall()) 0
4056 Out << "tail "; 0
4057 else if (CI->isNoTailCall()) 0
4058 Out << "notail "; 0
4059 } ----
4060 ----
4061 // Print out the opcode... ----
4062 Out << I.getOpcodeName(); 0
4063 ----
4064 // If this is an atomic load or store, print out the atomic marker. ----
4065 if ((isa(I) && cast(I).isAtomic()) || 0
4066 (isa(I) && cast(I).isAtomic())) 0
4067 Out << " atomic"; 0
4068 ----
4069 if (isa(I) && cast(I).isWeak()) 0
4070 Out << " weak"; 0
4071 ----
4072 // If this is a volatile operation, print out the volatile marker. ----
4073 if ((isa(I) && cast(I).isVolatile()) || 0
4074 (isa(I) && cast(I).isVolatile()) || 0
4075 (isa(I) && cast(I).isVolatile()) || 0
4076 (isa(I) && cast(I).isVolatile())) 0
4077 Out << " volatile"; 0
4078 ----
4079 // Print out optimization information. ----
4080 WriteOptimizationInfo(Out, &I); 0
4081 ----
4082 // Print out the compare instruction predicates ----
4083 if (const CmpInst *CI = dyn_cast(&I)) 0
4084 Out << ' ' << CI->getPredicate(); 0
4085 ----
4086 // Print out the atomicrmw operation ----
4087 if (const AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast(&I)) 0
4088 Out << ' ' << AtomicRMWInst::getOperationName(RMWI->getOperation()); 0
4089 ----
4090 // Print out the type of the operands... ----
4091 const Value *Operand = I.getNumOperands() ? I.getOperand(0) : nullptr; 0
4092 ----
4093 // Special case conditional branches to swizzle the condition out to the front ----
4094 if (isa(I) && cast(I).isConditional()) { 0
4095 const BranchInst &BI(cast(I)); 0
4096 Out << ' '; 0
4097 writeOperand(BI.getCondition(), true); 0
4098 Out << ", "; 0
4099 writeOperand(BI.getSuccessor(0), true); 0
4100 Out << ", "; 0
4101 writeOperand(BI.getSuccessor(1), true); 0
4102 ----
4103 } else if (isa(I)) { 0
4104 const SwitchInst& SI(cast(I)); 0
4105 // Special case switch instruction to get formatting nice and correct. ----
4106 Out << ' '; 0
4107 writeOperand(SI.getCondition(), true); 0
4108 Out << ", "; 0
4109 writeOperand(SI.getDefaultDest(), true); 0
4110 Out << " ["; 0
4111 for (auto Case : SI.cases()) { 0
4112 Out << "\n "; 0
4113 writeOperand(Case.getCaseValue(), true); 0
4114 Out << ", "; 0
4115 writeOperand(Case.getCaseSuccessor(), true); 0
4116 } ----
4117 Out << "\n ]"; 0
4118 } else if (isa(I)) { 0
4119 // Special case indirectbr instruction to get formatting nice and correct. ----
4120 Out << ' '; 0
4121 writeOperand(Operand, true); 0
4122 Out << ", ["; 0
4123 ----
4124 for (unsigned i = 1, e = I.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
4125 if (i != 1) 0
4126 Out << ", "; 0
4127 writeOperand(I.getOperand(i), true); 0
4128 } ----
4129 Out << ']'; 0
4130 } else if (const PHINode *PN = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4131 Out << ' '; 0
4132 TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out); 0
4133 Out << ' '; 0
4134 ----
4135 for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = PN->getNumIncomingValues(); op < Eop; ++op) { 0
4136 if (op) Out << ", "; 0
4137 Out << "[ "; 0
4138 writeOperand(PN->getIncomingValue(op), false); Out << ", "; 0
4139 writeOperand(PN->getIncomingBlock(op), false); Out << " ]"; 0
4140 } ----
4141 } else if (const ExtractValueInst *EVI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4142 Out << ' '; 0
4143 writeOperand(I.getOperand(0), true); 0
4144 for (unsigned i : EVI->indices()) 0
4145 Out << ", " << i; 0
4146 } else if (const InsertValueInst *IVI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4147 Out << ' '; 0
4148 writeOperand(I.getOperand(0), true); Out << ", "; 0
4149 writeOperand(I.getOperand(1), true); 0
4150 for (unsigned i : IVI->indices()) 0
4151 Out << ", " << i; 0
4152 } else if (const LandingPadInst *LPI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4153 Out << ' '; 0
4154 TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out); 0
4155 if (LPI->isCleanup() || LPI->getNumClauses() != 0) 0
4156 Out << '\n'; 0
4157 ----
4158 if (LPI->isCleanup()) 0
4159 Out << " cleanup"; 0
4160 ----
4161 for (unsigned i = 0, e = LPI->getNumClauses(); i != e; ++i) { 0
4162 if (i != 0 || LPI->isCleanup()) Out << "\n"; 0
4163 if (LPI->isCatch(i)) 0
4164 Out << " catch "; 0
4165 else ----
4166 Out << " filter "; 0
4167 ----
4168 writeOperand(LPI->getClause(i), true); 0
4169 } ----
4170 } else if (const auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4171 Out << " within "; 0
4172 writeOperand(CatchSwitch->getParentPad(), /*PrintType=*/false); 0
4173 Out << " ["; 0
4174 unsigned Op = 0; 0
4175 for (const BasicBlock *PadBB : CatchSwitch->handlers()) { 0
4176 if (Op > 0) 0
4177 Out << ", "; 0
4178 writeOperand(PadBB, /*PrintType=*/true); 0
4179 ++Op; 0
4180 } ----
4181 Out << "] unwind "; 0
4182 if (const BasicBlock *UnwindDest = CatchSwitch->getUnwindDest()) 0
4183 writeOperand(UnwindDest, /*PrintType=*/true); 0
4184 else ----
4185 Out << "to caller"; 0
4186 } else if (const auto *FPI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4187 Out << " within "; 0
4188 writeOperand(FPI->getParentPad(), /*PrintType=*/false); 0
4189 Out << " ["; 0
4190 for (unsigned Op = 0, NumOps = FPI->arg_size(); Op < NumOps; ++Op) { 0
4191 if (Op > 0) 0
4192 Out << ", "; 0
4193 writeOperand(FPI->getArgOperand(Op), /*PrintType=*/true); 0
4194 } ----
4195 Out << ']'; 0
4196 } else if (isa(I) && !Operand) { 0
4197 Out << " void"; 0
4198 } else if (const auto *CRI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4199 Out << " from "; 0
4200 writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(0), /*PrintType=*/false); 0
4201 ----
4202 Out << " to "; 0
4203 writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(1), /*PrintType=*/true); 0
4204 } else if (const auto *CRI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4205 Out << " from "; 0
4206 writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(0), /*PrintType=*/false); 0
4207 ----
4208 Out << " unwind "; 0
4209 if (CRI->hasUnwindDest()) 0
4210 writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(1), /*PrintType=*/true); 0
4211 else ----
4212 Out << "to caller"; 0
4213 } else if (const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4214 // Print the calling convention being used. ----
4215 if (CI->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::C) { 0
4216 Out << " "; 0
4217 PrintCallingConv(CI->getCallingConv(), Out); 0
4218 } ----
4219 ----
4220 Operand = CI->getCalledOperand(); 0
4221 FunctionType *FTy = CI->getFunctionType(); 0
4222 Type *RetTy = FTy->getReturnType(); 0
4223 const AttributeList &PAL = CI->getAttributes(); 0
4224 ----
4225 if (PAL.hasRetAttrs()) 0
4226 Out << ' ' << PAL.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex); 0
4227 ----
4228 // Only print addrspace(N) if necessary: ----
4229 maybePrintCallAddrSpace(Operand, &I, Out); 0
4230 ----
4231 // If possible, print out the short form of the call instruction. We can ----
4232 // only do this if the first argument is a pointer to a nonvararg function, ----
4233 // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function. ----
4234 Out << ' '; 0
4235 TypePrinter.print(FTy->isVarArg() ? FTy : RetTy, Out); 0
4236 Out << ' '; 0
4237 writeOperand(Operand, false); 0
4238 Out << '('; 0
4239 for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = CI->arg_size(); op < Eop; ++op) { 0
4240 if (op > 0) 0
4241 Out << ", "; 0
4242 writeParamOperand(CI->getArgOperand(op), PAL.getParamAttrs(op)); 0
4243 } ----
4244 ----
4245 // Emit an ellipsis if this is a musttail call in a vararg function. This ----
4246 // is only to aid readability, musttail calls forward varargs by default. ----
4247 if (CI->isMustTailCall() && CI->getParent() && 0

4251 Out << ", "; 0
4252 Out << "..."; 0
4253 } ----

4255 Out << ')'; 0
4256 if (PAL.hasFnAttrs()) 0
4257 Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(PAL.getFnAttrs()); 0
4258 ----
4259 writeOperandBundles(CI); 0
4260 } else if (const InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
4261 Operand = II->getCalledOperand(); 0

4271 ----
4272 if (PAL.hasRetAttrs()) 0
4273 Out << ' ' << PAL.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex); 0

4276 maybePrintCallAddrSpace(Operand, &I, Out); 0

4279 // only do this if the first argument is a pointer to a nonvararg function, ----
4280 // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function. ----
4281 // ----
4282 Out << ' '; 0
4283 TypePrinter.print(FTy->isVarArg() ? FTy : RetTy, Out); 0
4284 Out << ' '; 0
4285 writeOperand(Operand, false); 0

4289 Out << ", "; 0
4290 writeParamOperand(II->getArgOperand(op), PAL.getParamAttrs(op)); 0
4291 } ----
4292 ----
4293 Out << ')'; 0
4294 if (PAL.hasFnAttrs()) 0
4295 Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(PAL.getFnAttrs()); 0
4296 ----
4297 writeOperandBundles(II); 0

4300 writeOperand(II->getNormalDest(), true); 0

4302 writeOperand(II->getUnwindDest(), true); 0

4304 Operand = CBI->getCalledOperand(); 0

4320 // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function. ----
